20/06/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- Bosnia and Herzegovina's (BiH) Prime Minister Adnan Terzic met with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan on Thursday (19 June) to discuss the role of the UN mission in BiH and future plans for the country. 
Annan confirmed the UN would continue to support administrative reforms and projects under the UNDP.
During a week-long visit to the United States, Terzic also met with members of the US Congress. 
In addition, his delegation met with representatives of the IMF and the World Bank, seeking financial and technical support. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Oslobodjenje - 20/06/03)
